# ipam_routing_domain (Resource)

A routing domain is a logical grouping of IP ranges, typically corresponding to one or more GCP VPCs. Routing domains isolate address spaces so that allocations for one environment (e.g. `prod`) cannot overlap with another (e.g. `staging`).

When [Cloud Asset Inventory](https://cloud.google.com/asset-inventory) integration is enabled, the `vpcs` list scopes collision avoidance to the subnets belonging to those VPCs only.

## Example Usage

```hcl
resource "ipam_routing_domain" "prod" {
  name = "prod"
  vpcs = ["prod-vpc", "shared-vpc"]
}

resource "ipam_ip_range" "root" {
  name       = "prod-root"
  range_size = 16
  domain     = ipam_routing_domain.prod.id
}
```

{{ .SchemaMarkdown | trimspace }}

## Import

Routing domains can be imported using the numeric domain ID:

```bash
tofu import ipam_routing_domain.prod 1
```
